    <div class="recipe-content">
  
        
      <div class="recipe-info">
              
        <cite>
          Martha Stewart Living, March 2007        </cite>
                
        
                
                <ul class="clearfix">
        
                     
                    
         
                    <li class="yield">
            <strong>Yield</strong> Makes 8          </li>
                      
        </ul>
              </div>

            <div class="ingredients  recipe-section">
        <a href="#add-to-ziplist" class="add-ziplist">Add to Shopping List</a>        
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>  
        
  <div class="item-list"><ul class="content-multigroup-group-ingredient"><li class="ingredient first">  
    
          
                
        1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour</li>
<li class="ingredient">  
    
          
                
        1/2 cup good-quality unsweetened Dutch-process cocoa powder</li>
<li class="ingredient">  
    
          
                
        1 teaspoon baking powder</li>
<li class="ingredient">  
    
          
                
        1/2 teaspoon salt</li>
<li class="ingredient">  
    
          
                
        1/2 cup (1 stick) unsalted butter, softened</li>
<li class="ingredient">  
    
          
                
        1 1/2 cups sugar</li>
<li class="ingredient">  
    
          
                
        1/2 cup vegetable shortening, substitute 1/2 cup unsalted butter, melted and cooled</li>
<li class="ingredient">  
    
          
                
        1 large egg</li>
<li class="ingredient last">  
    
          
                
        1 1/2 teaspoons pure vanilla extract</li>
</ul></div>
      </div>
            
      
            <div class="recipe-section instructions">
        <h2>Directions</h2>
        
  <div class="item-list"><ol class="content-multigroup-group-steps"><li class="step first">  
    
          
                
        Preheat oven to 375. Whisk together flour, cocoa powder, baking powder, and salt in a medium bowl; set aside.</li>
<li class="step">  
    
          
                
        Put butter and sugar into the bowl of an electric mixer fitted with the paddle attachment. Mix on medium-high speed until pale and fluffy. Mix in shortening (or additional butter). Add egg and vanilla; mix until creamy. Reduce speed to low. Gradually add flour mixture, and mix until just combined.</li>
<li class="step last">  
    
          
                
        Using a 2 1/2-inch ice cream scoop, drop dough onto baking sheets lined with parchment paper, spacing about 4 inches apart. Bake until edges are firm, 18 to 20 minutes. Let cool on sheets on wire racks. Cookies can be stored in an airtight container up to 2 days.</li>
</ol></div>
      </div>
            
      <!--
      <p class="nutrition">
        <h4>Nutrition</h4>
      </p>
      -->
      
            
                    
         
